sentences: Eua Suntornsanan (Thai: เอื้อ สุนทรสนาน; RTGS: Uea Sunthonsanan; January 21, 1910, Amphawa, Samut Songkhram Province – April 1, 1981) was a singer, Thai composer and bandleader of Suntaraporn band.
Eua Suntornsanan (Thai: เอื้อ สุนทรสนาน; RTGS: Uea Sunthonsanan; January 21, 1910, Amphawa, Samut Songkhram Province – April 1, 1981) was a singer, Thai composer and bandleader of Suntaraporn band.
He composed over 2,000 songs that have been popular until today, for example, Rumwong Loy Kratong, many Songkran and New Year songs, and other Thai traditional songs.

Eua Suntornsanan was born on January 21, 1910, in Amphawa, Samut Songkhram Province.
He was receiving 20 baht per month for playing in the Big Band.
In 1936, Eua, at age 26, had a chance to perform an original soundtrack, phleng Thai sakol, that would also be used in a film.
When the company, Thai films, that he was working for was closed years after, he established a band called Suntaraporn band.
Eua’s band marked the beginning of the western-style music era in Thailand from the 1940s to the 1970s.
Eua’s band marked the beginning of the western-style music era in Thailand from the 1940s to the 1970s.
He retired in 1978 because of his illness, after 42 years of revolutionizing Thai music.

He died of cancer on April 1, 1981.
Eua Sunthornsanan married Arporn Karnasuta on May 14, 1946.
They had one daughter, Atiporn Suntornsanan, who now runs Suntaraporn Foundation with an aim to promote the life and work of Kru Eua Suntornsanan and Suntaraporn Band.
